If FAB is attached to the RecyclerView then onScrolled doesn't even get called. What I ended up using is the following workaround:

Do not attach FAB to the RecyclerView.
Use the following code in onScrolled:

```
    mRecyclerView.setOnScrollListener(new RecyclerView.OnScrollListener() {

        @Override
        public void onScrolled(RecyclerView recyclerView, int dx, int dy) {
            if (mLayoutManager.findFirstVisibleItemPosition() > lastKnownFirst) {
                mFab.hide(true);
            } else if (mLayoutManager.findFirstVisibleItemPosition() < lastKnownFirst) {
                mFab.show(true);
            }
            lastKnownFirst = mLayoutManager.findFirstVisibleItemPosition();
        }
    });
```

